1
00:01:02,827 --> 00:01:04,260
"My name is Michelle McNally"

2
00:01:04,863 --> 00:01:07,855
"The older child of an Anglo Indian
family based in Shimla"

3
00:01:11,136 --> 00:01:13,934
"This story is about me and my teacher"

4
00:01:14,906 --> 00:01:17,636
"A story about two people
left incomplete by god..."

5
00:01:18,476 --> 00:01:20,467
"who have fought a battle with fate..."

6
00:01:20,812 --> 00:01:22,871
"and made the impossible, possible"

7
00:01:24,049 --> 00:01:26,244
"The world in my story is different..."

8
00:01:27,586 --> 00:01:30,578
"where sound transcends into silence..."

9
00:01:33,558 --> 00:01:36,288
"and light into darkness"

10
00:01:38,363 --> 00:01:39,557
"This is my world"

11
00:01:40,198 --> 00:01:44,066
"Where nothing can be seen nor heard"

12
00:01:45,170 --> 00:01:49,129
"There is only one name for my world..."

13
00:02:01,586 --> 00:02:03,986
"How long can you live in this darkness?"

14
00:02:04,656 --> 00:02:08,456
"A few moments... hours... days?"

15
00:02:09,861 --> 00:02:12,955
"For 40 years I've lived
in this darkness..."

16
00:02:13,765 --> 00:02:16,928
"for 4 years I've given
my final B.A. Exam..."

17
00:02:18,003 --> 00:02:20,801
"and for twelve years, I've gone
to this church, every Sunday"

18
00:02:22,474 --> 00:02:24,203
"But that Sunday was special"

19
00:02:24,843 --> 00:02:28,142
"I felt God would answer my prayers..."

20
00:03:05,050 --> 00:03:07,610
"...my only prayer was..."

21
00:03:08,119 --> 00:03:11,816
"...that my teacher
would come back to me"

22
00:03:14,626 --> 00:03:19,563
"My prayers take long to reach God..."

23
00:03:20,665 --> 00:03:23,657
"and He takes long in granting them"

24
00:03:25,370 --> 00:03:27,304
"Even that Sunday I didn't
find my teacher"

25
00:03:28,506 --> 00:03:30,531
"That evening Sara and I were
returning home..."

26
00:03:31,042 --> 00:03:31,838
"...when suddenly..."

27
00:03:45,490 --> 00:03:46,286
Wait...

28
00:03:50,061 --> 00:03:51,995
Michelle, just wait for me, ok?

29
00:04:22,627 --> 00:04:23,423
Oh my God!

30
00:04:24,829 --> 00:04:29,789
MICHELLE!! MICHELLE!!

31
00:04:31,469 --> 00:04:34,597
MICHELLE!!
Your prayers have been answered...

32
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:38,140
it's Debraj... he's there
near the fountain,

33
00:04:39,911 --> 00:04:45,941
It's true, I promise, yes promise!
Come! Yes. Yes

34
00:05:10,175 --> 00:05:12,507
"That day my teacher came back to me..."

35
00:05:13,411 --> 00:05:16,005
"after 12 years I recognized him..."

36
00:05:16,381 --> 00:05:20,374
"but he had forgotten everything..."

37
00:05:21,786 --> 00:05:25,722
"even me"

38
00:05:26,457 --> 00:05:29,426
"I am writing this story for him..."

39
00:05:29,661 --> 00:05:32,061
"to my teacher - Debraj Sahai"

40
00:05:58,389 --> 00:06:00,357
He doesn't remember anything?

41
00:06:01,226 --> 00:06:02,955
Surely there must be something
we can do.

42
00:06:03,328 --> 00:06:07,731
Sara, Mr. Sahai has Alzheimer's disease.

43
00:06:07,999 --> 00:06:11,059
He has forgotten everything.
It's a very scary void.

44
00:06:11,536 --> 00:06:14,801
Mr. Sahai has even forgotten his bed.

45
00:06:15,073 --> 00:06:19,840
He has forgotten words,
even forgotten how to speak.

46
00:06:22,213 --> 00:06:24,875
No doctor. I refuse to believe this...

47
00:06:25,550 --> 00:06:27,177
he must remember something...

48
00:06:27,852 --> 00:06:31,652
otherwise, after all these years,
to find him at our house...

49
00:06:33,558 --> 00:06:36,459
and Mr. Sahai can
never forget Michelle.

50
00:06:37,695 --> 00:06:40,687
Like a duster wipes the words
of a blackboard...

51
00:06:41,432 --> 00:06:45,926
the disease has slowly
wiped out all his memories.

52
00:06:46,471 --> 00:06:51,568
A few words or instances
might spark some memory...

53
00:06:52,243 --> 00:06:53,870
but Alzheimer's has no cure.

54
00:06:55,513 --> 00:06:56,571
What is Michelle doing?

55
00:06:57,982 --> 00:07:01,850
She wants to read to him
her life story, in Braille.

56
00:07:03,221 --> 00:07:08,853
Maybe by touching those words
he might remember something...

57
00:07:09,727 --> 00:07:12,958
Michelle believes
that this miracle will happen.

58
00:07:17,936 --> 00:07:19,563
Science doesn't believe in miracles.

59
00:07:20,138 --> 00:07:22,106
It is impossible for him
to remember anything...

60
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:27,605
Impossible is one word that
Mr. Sahai never taught Michelle

61
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:31,348
And what you call impossible...

62
00:07:32,150 --> 00:07:34,641
she will make possible.

63
00:07:35,553 --> 00:07:38,078
"You were written in my destiny..."

64
00:07:38,456 --> 00:07:40,083
"when I was 2 years old"

65
00:07:40,458 --> 00:07:48,194
"That night suddenly
all happiness left us..."

66
00:07:48,866 --> 00:07:50,834
"when my life entered a black vaccuum"

67
00:07:51,269 --> 00:07:55,797
Michelle... my beautiful baby.

68
00:07:56,441 --> 00:08:00,104
You're not sick anymore...
now you can play in water.

69
00:08:02,613 --> 00:08:07,448
Look who has come! Papa!
What has the doctor told papa?

70
00:08:07,785 --> 00:08:11,653
The doctor has said that
Michelle can't see or hear.

71
00:08:16,794 --> 00:08:17,818
What did you say?

72
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:21,694
Our Michelle has gone
blind and deaf.

73
00:08:37,982 --> 00:08:40,746
Look at me! Michelle!

74
00:09:11,716 --> 00:09:13,684
"I was like an animal"

75
00:09:14,419 --> 00:09:16,751
"Children loved playing pranks on me."

76
00:09:17,622 --> 00:09:19,385
"So did God."

77
00:09:20,358 --> 00:09:23,657
Mrs. Gomes! Who has tied
these cans on Michelle?

78
00:09:25,797 --> 00:09:27,992
Shh... calm down Michelle,
calm down, baby calm down.

79
00:09:44,182 --> 00:09:46,377
Fire! Fire! Mrs. McNally. Fire!

80
00:09:46,584 --> 00:09:50,486
Help Mrs. McNally
Help. Mrs. McNally

81
00:09:54,592 --> 00:09:57,925
For eight years... every day
a new accident

82
00:09:58,062 --> 00:10:01,395
Hurting someone with a knife,
or breaking her own head!

83
00:10:01,666 --> 00:10:03,327
She could have burnt
the whole house down.

84
00:10:03,534 --> 00:10:06,469
With Michelle, we can never be happy.

85
00:10:06,671 --> 00:10:07,933
What are you trying to say?

86
00:10:08,139 --> 00:10:10,972
We will send her to an institution.

87
00:10:11,375 --> 00:10:14,367
You mean a mental asylum?

88
00:10:15,413 --> 00:10:17,745
How can you think that?

89
00:10:17,949 --> 00:10:21,009
Cathy, I love her just as much.

90
00:10:21,285 --> 00:10:22,616
But I still want to send her away.

91
00:10:23,254 --> 00:10:25,586
She could cause irreparable damage.

92
00:10:25,790 --> 00:10:28,384
No. I'm sorry. I don't agree.

93
00:10:28,593 --> 00:10:31,061
There is no other solution.

94
00:10:31,262 --> 00:10:33,822
I have no more patience left.

95
00:10:35,032 --> 00:10:38,490
Sara! Oh my God!

96
00:10:39,337 --> 00:10:43,171
Enough of this!
This child will be the death of us.

97
00:10:43,841 --> 00:10:44,500
Paul, leave her!

98
00:10:44,709 --> 00:10:48,668
She will not stay her another moment.
She almost... killed Sara.

99
00:10:51,949 --> 00:10:54,884
Let her go!

100
00:10:55,052 --> 00:11:02,288
It's not her fault.
For God's sake!

101
00:11:02,793 --> 00:11:04,624
Try and understand her.

102
00:11:06,430 --> 00:11:09,194
She is suffering.

103
00:11:12,003 --> 00:11:14,870
She is suffocating
in her own darkness.

104
00:11:18,009 --> 00:11:19,533
My baby is suffering

105
00:11:28,753 --> 00:11:30,846
There's this school in Dehradun...

106
00:11:31,522 --> 00:11:34,548
where children like Michelle
are given special training.

107
00:11:35,126 --> 00:11:37,890
If you let me,
I can write for a teacher...

108
00:11:38,095 --> 00:11:39,995
We do not need a teacher...

109
00:11:40,731 --> 00:11:41,925
We need a magician.

110
00:11:42,934 --> 00:11:46,961
I don't want to hear anymore
that there is no cure for our Michelle.

111
00:11:47,171 --> 00:11:48,433
One Last time Paul.

112
00:11:49,473 --> 00:11:51,338
Maybe this is the teacher
who is the magician...

113
00:11:52,043 --> 00:11:54,910
who will bring light
into our Michelle's life.

114
00:12:06,457 --> 00:12:07,219
Debraj.

115
00:12:09,227 --> 00:12:15,723
Ah, Ms. Nair. Come into the light.

116
00:12:17,134 --> 00:12:20,729
What are you doing, Debraj?
You've just had your eyes operated.

117
00:12:20,938 --> 00:12:24,101
And now what are you doing
holding a dying bulb?

118
00:12:24,475 --> 00:12:28,707
This bulb is dying, Ms. Nair.
I need to stand by it

119
00:12:30,548 --> 00:12:31,014
Am I right?

120
00:12:33,618 --> 00:12:36,849
It's... it's dying.

121
00:12:40,625 --> 00:12:43,116
You've been drinking again all day.
Haven't you, Debraj?

122
00:12:43,327 --> 00:12:44,851
No, no...

123
00:12:46,163 --> 00:12:51,066
Trying to find a sign for light.
For my deaf and blind children...

124
00:12:52,770 --> 00:12:55,432
whose light has been
taken away from them.

125
00:12:55,506 --> 00:13:04,539
Light... LIGHT!

126
00:13:04,882 --> 00:13:09,649
Just spell it, Debraj.
L.I.G.H.T. Light

127
00:13:09,854 --> 00:13:13,551
Ah! The difference between
a teacher... and a magician.

128
00:13:14,191 --> 00:13:16,386
You make me so angry sometimes Debraj.

129
00:13:16,661 --> 00:13:18,629
Angry... Angry

130
00:13:19,130 --> 00:13:20,654
Stop this bullshit

131
00:13:20,865 --> 00:13:25,302
Bullshit Bullshit
Bull. Bull... Bull... shit Bull... shit

132
00:13:25,503 --> 00:13:30,998
I do not have time for your talks.
I have some very important news for you.

133
00:13:31,208 --> 00:13:36,874
Three guesses... if it's my termination
letter, put it in the third drawer.

134
00:13:37,081 --> 00:13:39,049
If it's my last salary,
then it goes here in my pocket...

135
00:13:39,250 --> 00:13:42,617
and if it's a notice to vacate this room
then throw it in the dustbin.

136
00:13:42,820 --> 00:13:45,687
And. On your way to any of
these Ms Nair... could you please

137
00:13:45,890 --> 00:13:48,950
fetch me my... eye-drops... from that
table over there. Thank you.

138
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:51,060
You may have three guesses Debraj...

139
00:13:51,329 --> 00:13:53,923
but you have only one choice.
This letter.

140
00:13:54,865 --> 00:13:58,096
An eight-year girl,
in Shimla, Michelle.

141
00:13:58,903 --> 00:14:02,703
She can't see, she can't hear and
her parents don't understand her.

142
00:14:03,741 --> 00:14:05,709
You are their last hope Debraj.

143
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:08,273
Otherwise they will put her
in the asylum.

144
00:14:08,646 --> 00:14:13,345
You are the best teacher I know.
She needs a teacher, you need a job.

145
00:14:13,951 --> 00:14:14,440
Look up

146
00:14:17,822 --> 00:14:19,881
What do you see in this eye, Ms. Nair?

147
00:14:21,525 --> 00:14:22,549
A great love for me.

148
00:14:22,827 --> 00:14:24,988
You need to get your eyes checked.

149
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:31,393
And this one?
- Nothing

150
00:14:31,869 --> 00:14:33,632
Her name is Michelle, isn't it?

151
00:14:38,342 --> 00:14:39,969
I can see everything clearly.

152
00:14:42,179 --> 00:14:43,840
A beautiful morning...

153
00:14:45,649 --> 00:14:47,139
snow covered streets...

154
00:14:48,552 --> 00:14:50,019
and that little girl...

155
00:14:51,021 --> 00:14:55,048
a lost soul, directionless.

156
00:14:56,093 --> 00:15:01,895
I will give her wings
made of words, Ms. Nair.

157
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:05,433
I will teach her how to fly.

158
00:15:05,636 --> 00:15:11,700
You couldn't do anything for yourself
and you're out to change others' lives

159
00:15:12,576 --> 00:15:15,272
What happened, do your eyes hurt?

160
00:15:15,479 --> 00:15:18,778
No, not my eyes...

161
00:15:20,151 --> 00:15:24,645
my heart hurts...

162
00:15:30,428 --> 00:15:38,528
listening to your cruel words...

163
00:15:40,504 --> 00:15:47,808
it hurts... it hurts!

164
00:15:51,348 --> 00:15:54,749
That after spending thirty years
in this school...

165
00:15:54,952 --> 00:16:02,825
I'm just an unseen unheard entity.

166
00:16:04,528 --> 00:16:09,864
When I saw the school
for the last time...

167
00:16:10,167 --> 00:16:16,265
my students were waving to me
in the wrong direction.

168
00:16:19,176 --> 00:16:23,738
Waving to me in the
wrong direction Ms. Nair.

169
00:16:26,717 --> 00:16:32,417
Oh! Lt... it... it... hurts...

170
00:16:35,659 --> 00:16:36,353
it hurts.

171
00:16:43,367 --> 00:16:45,631
"Destiny had put together
two strange soul- mates."

172
00:16:46,837 --> 00:16:49,431
"I was left incomplete by god..."

173
00:16:50,708 --> 00:16:53,370
"and you were
a battle - weary warrior."

174
00:16:57,314 --> 00:16:59,145
"I was waiting in my darkness..."

175
00:17:00,284 --> 00:17:02,775
"and you were bringing
the flickering light."

176
00:17:12,997 --> 00:17:15,693
Right. Where's the girl?

177
00:17:16,166 --> 00:17:19,294
This is all we needed.
An alcoholic teacher.

178
00:17:23,707 --> 00:17:31,478
Mmmm... lnteresting.
Playful, bit of a brat.

179
00:17:36,086 --> 00:17:37,212
And very pretty...

180
00:17:56,774 --> 00:18:01,268
Yes. Yes... someone new...
a new buddy.

181
00:18:09,186 --> 00:18:14,783
You like my glasses, don't you?
Well... you can have them...

182
00:18:15,526 --> 00:18:17,926
here... there you go.

183
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:23,858
Happy?

184
00:18:27,504 --> 00:18:30,473
Teacher... Tea... cher

185
00:18:33,911 --> 00:18:36,277
Mr. Sahai, she understands?

186
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:39,506
No, she's just imitating me.

187
00:18:39,817 --> 00:18:43,275
Good... good girl

188
00:18:50,761 --> 00:18:51,386
What is she doing?

189
00:18:51,629 --> 00:18:54,792
That's her sign for me.
Her mother

190
00:18:54,999 --> 00:19:00,494
Oh, she's strong.
- I'm really sorry, Mr. Sahai

191
00:19:00,704 --> 00:19:01,500
It's alright.

192
00:19:03,907 --> 00:19:07,104
What's this!!
What is this bell for?

193
00:19:07,411 --> 00:19:09,106
This is her identity

194
00:19:09,580 --> 00:19:12,344
If she is lost.
We find her through its sound.

195
00:19:13,384 --> 00:19:14,578
Take it off!!!!

196
00:19:18,722 --> 00:19:22,249
When you think, that
your child is an animal...

197
00:19:22,393 --> 00:19:28,263
what do you expect of others?
- It's your job to make her human.

198
00:19:28,966 --> 00:19:30,661
How do you plan to do this?

199
00:19:31,969 --> 00:19:33,197
These Fingers, Mr. McNally.

200
00:19:34,838 --> 00:19:36,135
They're eyes of the blind...

201
00:19:36,940 --> 00:19:38,134
...Voice of the mute...

202
00:19:39,309 --> 00:19:40,799
poetry of the deaf.

203
00:19:42,846 --> 00:19:44,746
Raise it to a sword...

204
00:19:45,516 --> 00:19:47,143
...clench it for strength.

205
00:19:48,052 --> 00:19:49,349
They can feed you and slap you,

206
00:19:50,087 --> 00:19:51,850
They can point you towards God
and sometimes...

207
00:19:52,122 --> 00:19:52,816
even the door.

208
00:19:54,992 --> 00:20:00,897
It isn't as easy as you make it seem.
My daughter is like me...

209
00:20:01,432 --> 00:20:03,366
stubborn...
- Insolent.

210
00:20:04,835 --> 00:20:06,598
Not you. Your daughter

211
00:20:06,804 --> 00:20:09,466
Lunch... will be served
shortly, Mr. Sahai.

212
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:12,070
Thank you. Mrs. McNally,
I'm so hungry.

213
00:20:21,151 --> 00:20:23,176
Thank you Lord, for the bread
on our plate

214
00:20:24,354 --> 00:20:27,949
for the air we breathe,
so fresh and pure.

215
00:20:28,492 --> 00:20:31,325
For kindness and faith,
we are thankful to Thee.

216
00:20:32,463 --> 00:20:36,957
Life's treasures and loved ones,
we hold and cherish.

217
00:20:47,478 --> 00:20:48,410
No

218
00:20:48,812 --> 00:20:50,712
Leave her, Mr. Sahai.

219
00:20:51,048 --> 00:20:53,846
No. She has to learn how to behave.

220
00:20:54,284 --> 00:20:56,844
Leave her hand Mr. Sahai!

221
00:20:57,054 --> 00:21:00,319
This is the only reason
she hasn't learnt anything.

222
00:21:01,258 --> 00:21:04,887
I will not tolerate this
in front of my guests.

223
00:21:05,062 --> 00:21:07,963
Michelle eats like this.

224
00:21:09,032 --> 00:21:12,399
Either she eats from her plate
or stays hungry. Am I understood?

225
00:21:13,137 --> 00:21:16,038
Let her eat, you will
get another plate.

226
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:19,698
I... don't have a problem
with the plate, Mr. McNally.

227
00:21:19,910 --> 00:21:21,537
The plate... is fine.

228
00:21:21,745 --> 00:21:23,940
Let her go.
This is no way to teach.

229
00:21:24,148 --> 00:21:26,776
Don't you feel pity
for this handicapped child?

230
00:21:27,084 --> 00:21:31,885
Pity? And on this devil?
So she can do as she pleases?

231
00:21:32,089 --> 00:21:34,284
No Mr. McNally,
I have pity on you...

232
00:21:34,491 --> 00:21:36,459
and don't you dare
call her handicapped.

233
00:21:36,660 --> 00:21:43,088
That's enough! Do not forget that you
are a paid servant in this house.

234
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:47,464
A Teacher! Mr. McNally... not a
paid servant... A paid teacher.

235
00:21:47,671 --> 00:21:49,571
Leave her, right now.

236
00:21:49,773 --> 00:21:51,138
No! You leave. All of you.

237
00:21:51,341 --> 00:21:52,899
Mr. Sahai,
handling Michelle like this...

238
00:21:53,110 --> 00:21:56,238
Mrs. McNally... you had said that
you'd cooperate.

239
00:21:56,513 --> 00:21:58,310
All right. There's no point in
going on like this.

240
00:21:58,515 --> 00:22:01,313
Let's give him a chance.
Let him do his job Paul.

241
00:22:01,518 --> 00:22:05,147
Leave! Leave!

242
00:22:19,970 --> 00:22:22,438
Martha, I'm really sorry,
for today's lunch

243
00:22:22,639 --> 00:22:24,106
Don't worry Cathy.

244
00:22:24,341 --> 00:22:27,435
He's a new teacher, that's why.
Isn't it, Paul?

245
00:22:27,911 --> 00:22:29,606
Martha, I'll drop you home.

246
00:22:32,382 --> 00:22:33,576
Paul, I will speak to Mr. Sahai...

247
00:22:39,289 --> 00:22:41,849
I am very hungry;
I am going to eat...

248
00:22:42,793 --> 00:22:47,127
and if you behave
then you can eat too.

249
00:23:03,780 --> 00:23:04,337
Spoon!

250
00:23:07,517 --> 00:23:10,748
No. You will not use
your hands to eat your food.

251
00:23:10,954 --> 00:23:13,980
