00:45:27,690 --> 00:45:29,248
I will not give up so easily.

496
00:45:29,458 --> 00:45:31,392
I have kept my promise.
Now it's your turn.

497
00:45:31,594 --> 00:45:35,086
But it's not yet over Mrs. McNally.
There are still a few minutes left.

498
00:45:35,297 --> 00:45:37,993
Paul can come at any moment.
Mr. Sahai. I'm helpless

499
00:45:38,200 --> 00:45:39,667
Yes. Mrs. McNally.
But she has to learn.

500
00:45:39,868 --> 00:45:41,859
Mr. Sahai...
- She has to learn...

501
00:45:42,071 --> 00:45:47,008
that the hand she is holding has a name.
That you are mother, mother...

502
00:45:47,810 --> 00:45:51,405
M.O.T.H.E. R... mother.

503
00:45:56,919 --> 00:45:57,749
And that is FATHER.

504
00:46:02,391 --> 00:46:04,586
Paul, I was just...
- Leave, Mr. Sahai.

505
00:46:30,519 --> 00:46:33,352
Dear Ms. Nair, you will be
delighted to know...

506
00:46:33,555 --> 00:46:38,618
that after having spent 20 days
with little Michelle, I have failed.

507
00:46:39,695 --> 00:46:43,893
However, if you're smiling at the
thought of looking into my eyes again...

508
00:46:44,600 --> 00:46:46,124
you are terribly mistaken.

509
00:46:56,612 --> 00:46:58,739
Mrs. Gomes, will you stop her?

510
00:46:59,381 --> 00:47:02,646
Let her be Mr. Sahai.
She's very happy today

511
00:47:06,555 --> 00:47:09,251
No! Stop it Michelle.
You little brat.

512
00:47:10,893 --> 00:47:12,758
I am not going to allow you
to do this to me.

513
00:47:14,530 --> 00:47:15,997
I might have been asked to leave...

514
00:47:16,198 --> 00:47:19,895
but I am not going to leave you
to behave like this.

515
00:47:24,406 --> 00:47:26,340
Stop it Michelle.
Stop it!

516
00:47:26,542 --> 00:47:30,103
You won't forget what I've
taught you in 20 days... sit down

517
00:47:30,312 --> 00:47:30,778
Please leave her Mr. Sahai,
let her be.

518
00:47:30,979 --> 00:47:32,139
Sit... sit down.

519
00:47:32,848 --> 00:47:38,184
You will use this napkin on your
neck and use a spoon... to eat.

520
00:47:38,387 --> 00:47:40,685
Mo you are not going to throw...

521
00:48:03,846 --> 00:48:05,245
Come on, Come here...

522
00:48:06,448 --> 00:48:09,747
You brat... you want to
throw water at me!

523
00:48:10,219 --> 00:48:14,280
Let me teach you what water is!
Come here! What water is, come on!

524
00:48:15,324 --> 00:48:20,990
This is water... water... water...

525
00:48:21,196 --> 00:48:25,997
Give me your hand... This is woah...
Water... water... Understand?

526
00:48:26,201 --> 00:48:26,826
Woah!!

527
00:48:31,306 --> 00:48:31,829
Woah!

528
00:49:52,221 --> 00:49:55,816
Water... it's water...

529
00:49:56,058 --> 00:50:01,189
W.A.T.E.R.

530
00:50:23,919 --> 00:50:25,011
Mrs. McNally!!!

531
00:50:32,494 --> 00:50:38,433
Yes... this is 'Grass'.
G.R.A.S.S. Spell it...

532
00:50:41,069 --> 00:50:43,560
Very good... Very good...
Mrs. McNally!!!

533
00:50:45,274 --> 00:50:52,146
That's 'FLOWER' flower...
flower... F.L.O.W.E. R... flower.

534
00:50:52,514 --> 00:50:58,384
Mrs. McNally!! Mr. McNally!!
Mr. McNally!! Mr. McNally!!

535
00:51:00,055 --> 00:51:03,491
What's wrong Mr. Sahai?
Is Michelle all right?

536
00:51:03,692 --> 00:51:07,389
Michelle. Michelle she...
Mrs. McNally. She knows, she knows.

537
00:51:07,596 --> 00:51:08,620
She knows the meaning of words.

538
00:51:08,830 --> 00:51:11,856
She actually. Actually
knows the meaning of words.

539
00:51:12,067 --> 00:51:13,830
Look. Look!

540
00:51:16,805 --> 00:51:21,833
Yes, Michelle...
Mother. Mother...

541
00:51:39,494 --> 00:51:40,051
Maa...

542
00:51:54,176 --> 00:51:55,006
Mother

543
00:51:56,178 --> 00:51:56,769
Maa...

544
00:51:57,579 --> 00:51:58,876
Once more

545
00:52:00,749 --> 00:52:01,477
Ma...

546
00:52:06,822 --> 00:52:07,982
Pa... Pa...

547
00:52:48,803 --> 00:52:55,231
This is 'Teacher'. "Tea... cher"

548
00:52:59,214 --> 00:53:08,179
Tee... Tee

549
00:53:09,557 --> 00:53:11,923
Yes... Yes

550
00:53:12,227 --> 00:53:14,354
Yes, he's your Tee

551
00:53:32,747 --> 00:53:34,044
Dear Ms. Nair...

552
00:53:40,055 --> 00:53:41,647
You'll be happy to know...

553
00:53:44,759 --> 00:53:51,995
that I have... I have...

554
00:54:19,694 --> 00:54:22,891
"That day you had won your
first battle over my darkness."

555
00:54:24,666 --> 00:54:26,463
"But today you don't
remember anything."

556
00:54:27,969 --> 00:54:29,903
"Now I will fight
against your darkness."

557
00:54:31,239 --> 00:54:35,403
"I'll teach you everything
you taught me"

558
00:55:35,570 --> 00:55:39,062
"Water. The first word
that you taught me..."

559
00:55:39,641 --> 00:55:42,075
"and after that..."

560
00:55:43,077 --> 00:55:48,982
"you typed every little
detail on my hand..."

561
00:55:49,484 --> 00:55:53,147
"like a maestro playing a symphony"

562
00:55:56,291 --> 00:55:57,019
Cathy!

563
00:55:58,059 --> 00:56:00,687
Martha... Martha!
When did you return from London?

564
00:56:00,895 --> 00:56:04,854
Oh! It's so good to see you.
Merry Christmas.

565
00:56:07,168 --> 00:56:10,729
Mr. McNally...
- Coming, Mr Sahai. Just a moment

566
00:56:11,573 --> 00:56:16,533
I'd like you to meet Mr. Fernandez,
principal of the King Edward University.

567
00:56:16,744 --> 00:56:19,235
I want Michelle to study
in their college

568
00:56:19,447 --> 00:56:21,210
It's an honor to meet you,
Mr. Fernandez.

569
00:56:21,416 --> 00:56:22,041
It's a pleasure sir.

570
00:56:22,550 --> 00:56:24,211
I don't believe how time
has passed, Martha

571
00:56:24,419 --> 00:56:27,980
Let me prove it to you...
Hello... Come

572
00:56:31,526 --> 00:56:36,520
Did you recognize her?
My younger daughter, Sara

573
00:56:37,232 --> 00:56:40,133
Sara, this is aunt Martha,
an old friend of mine

574
00:56:40,335 --> 00:56:40,801
Oh! Hello, aunt Martha.
I've heard so...

575
00:56:41,002 --> 00:56:43,402
But where is my dear Michelle?
I can't wait to see her

576
00:56:43,605 --> 00:56:45,368
Ah Michelle.
Have you seen Michelle?

577
00:56:46,007 --> 00:56:51,877
Err! Yes... I think
she's inside, excuse me.

578
00:56:54,549 --> 00:56:55,709
Come... we'll go look for her.

579
00:57:25,380 --> 00:57:26,278
Ah! There she is

580
00:58:23,004 --> 00:58:26,906
Mr. Sahai. Look at that girl.
She can't hear or see,

581
00:58:27,108 --> 00:58:30,100
And still... just look at her,
it's wonderful.

582
00:58:32,146 --> 00:58:33,636
That's Michelle McNally...

583
00:58:36,284 --> 00:58:40,186
the girl I was talking about.
- That's impossible Mr. Sahai.

584
00:58:40,388 --> 00:58:44,324
Impossible is a word that I have
never taught her Mr. Fernandez.

585
00:58:44,892 --> 00:58:47,087
There are special schools
for such children...

586
00:58:47,595 --> 00:58:49,927
where they are taught many things.

587
00:58:51,632 --> 00:58:55,534
To make baskets, weave carpets...

588
00:58:56,838 --> 00:59:01,866
Have you heard of a girl like Michelle
getting admission in a normal college?

589
00:59:02,076 --> 00:59:05,102
No, but I would love to.

590
00:59:05,313 --> 00:59:07,645
How will she understand the lectures?

591
00:59:07,849 --> 00:59:12,946
I will sit with her in the classroom.
She will learn everything through signs

592
00:59:13,187 --> 00:59:15,382
Every word, every letter.

593
00:59:17,658 --> 00:59:23,494
Michelle... meet your Principal

594
00:59:29,470 --> 00:59:35,102
Yes yes... I've told him... you
want admission in arts, not science

595
00:59:36,010 --> 00:59:40,174
Mr. Sahai I will have to consult
the trustees on this.

596
00:59:40,381 --> 00:59:45,478
You get few chances for good deeds.

597
00:59:46,054 --> 00:59:49,046
And I hope that you will
not lose this opportunity.

598
00:59:52,060 --> 00:59:52,719
Cheers?

599
00:59:55,396 --> 01:00:01,028
Mr. Sahai, you know this university
is for normal students.

600
01:00:01,569 --> 01:00:04,197
But because of your faith
in Michelle...

601
01:00:04,405 --> 01:00:06,339
and because we believe
you are a good teacher...

602
01:00:06,541 --> 01:00:09,738
We will interview Michelle.
- Thank you.

603
01:00:10,011 --> 01:00:12,377
But today, you cannot
interpret for Michelle.

604
01:00:12,780 --> 01:00:17,911
We have called a special teacher,
who doesn't know either of you.

605
01:00:18,219 --> 01:00:19,345
She will interpret.

606
01:00:19,554 --> 01:00:22,250
They will interview you.
Another interpreter, not me, ok?

607
01:00:29,397 --> 01:00:30,864
Ah, there she is.

608
01:00:35,036 --> 01:00:35,593
Mrs Nair?

609
01:00:36,237 --> 01:00:38,705
Welcome Ms. Nair, meet Mr. Sahai.

610
01:00:39,440 --> 01:00:40,702
Hello, Ms. Nair.
- Hello.

611
01:00:40,908 --> 01:00:42,034
Light

612
01:00:52,153 --> 01:00:55,213
Are you ready for the interview?

613
01:00:57,592 --> 01:00:58,616
We're ready, Sir.

614
01:01:02,130 --> 01:01:04,155
Why does she want to study?

615
01:01:04,632 --> 01:01:06,964
Why do you want to study?

616
01:01:08,669 --> 01:01:11,900
I want to study... and learn...

617
01:01:12,473 --> 01:01:18,275
so that I may live with dignity,
with independence... and to be alive.

618
01:01:19,113 --> 01:01:20,740
How many oceans are
there in the world?

619
01:01:20,948 --> 01:01:24,008
How many oceans are
there in the world?

620
01:01:25,586 --> 01:01:32,424
For me every drop of water is an ocean

621
01:01:32,627 --> 01:01:37,087
She is not answering my question.
How many oceans are there in the world?

622
01:01:37,298 --> 01:01:40,756
They want a straight answer
to their question

623
01:01:47,608 --> 01:01:51,601
If we are in India,
on which side will America be?

624
01:01:51,812 --> 01:01:54,212
If you are in India,
which side is America?

625
01:02:14,235 --> 01:02:20,970
The world is round.
So America can be on any side.

626
01:02:23,744 --> 01:02:27,646
What does knowledge mean to her?
- What does knowledge mean to you?

627
01:02:30,518 --> 01:02:33,078
Knowledge... is everything

628
01:02:34,021 --> 01:02:41,894
Knowledge is spirit, wisdom,
courage, light, sound.

629
01:02:43,564 --> 01:02:46,727
Knowledge is my Bible, God...

630
01:02:48,202 --> 01:02:49,328
Tee!

631
01:02:49,837 --> 01:02:55,434
...knowledge is my teacher
- Bravo! Excellent.

632
01:03:01,215 --> 01:03:02,682
Congratulations, Mr. Sahai.

633
01:03:03,351 --> 01:03:06,684
Your student is now a
part of our university.

634
01:03:11,892 --> 01:03:15,521
Thank you... Thank you

635
01:03:24,071 --> 01:03:25,368
I answered every question they asked.

636
01:03:26,474 --> 01:03:31,639
Michelle looks so happy today Paul.
Can't stop talking about the interview

637
01:03:32,913 --> 01:03:35,040
She hasn't stopped smiling all day.

638
01:03:35,249 --> 01:03:39,652
Why not? A girl who couldn't
sit at the dining table...

639
01:03:40,488 --> 01:03:45,551
has a seat in the university today.
Unbelievable.

640
01:03:45,760 --> 01:03:52,723
Can you imagine? Can you imagine the day
when we see Michelle as a graduate?

641
01:03:53,334 --> 01:03:57,065
Ah, it's going to be such a
special day, isn't it Sara?

642
01:03:58,606 --> 01:03:59,732
Yes, of course, mama.

643
01:04:00,508 --> 01:04:03,409
Whatever Michelle does is always special.
Isn't it?

644
01:04:04,745 --> 01:04:06,906
Excuse me;
I need to finish my sketch.

645
01:04:14,855 --> 01:04:16,584
Good evening Sara.
- Good evening.

646
01:04:17,124 --> 01:04:21,083
Mr. Sahai, congratulations.
You have performed yet...

647
01:04:21,295 --> 01:04:25,254
another miracle.
Still a long way to go, Mr. McNally

648
01:04:26,100 --> 01:04:29,365
The journey has just begun.

649
01:04:32,306 --> 01:04:33,273
Teacher!

650
01:04:37,311 --> 01:04:40,769
She's been waiting for
her gift for so long.

651
01:04:52,827 --> 01:04:54,294
What is this?

652
01:04:56,063 --> 01:04:59,521
Your friend, for... life.

653
01:05:00,167 --> 01:05:05,036
I don't need

654
01:05:06,507 --> 01:05:07,974
I don't want to be dependent on this.

655
01:05:10,177 --> 01:05:14,409
This will not make you dependent.

656
01:05:15,983 --> 01:05:21,114
It will make you independent.
Do you understand?

657
01:05:57,124 --> 01:05:59,115
"It was the beginning of a new life..."

658
01:05:59,760 --> 01:06:02,695
"a new feeling, a new horizon..."

659
01:06:03,397 --> 01:06:04,864
"You had faith in me..."

660
01:06:05,399 --> 01:06:07,367
"and I had faith in my wings."

661
01:06:07,768 --> 01:06:11,033
Remember how happy I was
that day?

662
01:06:21,081 --> 01:06:24,608
Is it wise to let Michelle live alone?

663
01:06:24,819 --> 01:06:27,720
She is not alone;
Mrs. Gomes will also live here.

664
01:06:27,922 --> 01:06:29,890
I will also live next door.

665
01:06:30,624 --> 01:06:35,891
University is close by,
she will meet new people.

666
01:06:36,163 --> 01:06:40,759
Besides, we can't protect
her all her life.

667
01:06:40,968 --> 01:06:42,230
Don't worry. She'll be fine!

668
01:06:42,436 --> 01:06:43,733
What's wrong with you, Sara? Huh?

669
01:06:43,938 --> 01:06:45,803
We were all just laughing
now suddenly you're fighting.

670
01:06:46,006 --> 01:06:48,736
It's very irritating, mama.
Anything that I put anywhere...

671
01:06:48,943 --> 01:06:50,342
she picks it up and puts it
somewhere else.

672
01:06:51,312 --> 01:06:52,904
Ma, I love her very much,
I really do.

673
01:06:53,113 --> 01:06:55,411
But... Please... leave me
out of this. Ok?

674
01:06:55,950 --> 01:06:58,748
She's very excited, sweetie.
Please understand

675
01:06:58,953 --> 01:07:01,478
I understand everything.
It's always about her, right?

676
01:07:01,689 --> 01:07:04,852
Her excitement, her happiness, she's
the one who means everything to you

677
01:07:05,326 --> 01:07:09,057
But what about me?
Should I speak to you in sign language?

678
01:07:09,263 --> 01:07:11,197
Paul, I can't believe
what she's saying.

679
01:07:14,268 --> 01:07:16,702
Oh My God...
Michelle!

680
01:07:18,138 --> 01:07:21,505
Michelle!
- No, Mrs. McNally. Leave her alone.

681
01:07:23,344 --> 01:07:26,108
With every fall, she'll rise higher.

682
01:07:27,147 --> 01:07:30,116
I fell.

683
01:07:31,018 --> 01:07:32,076
That's the spirit.

684
01:07:34,488 --> 01:07:41,519
I want you to walk alone,
without any help.

685
01:07:43,030 --> 01:07:47,797
then right. Understood?

686
01:08:02,983 --> 01:08:05,315
JoJo... go slow... l'm getting old.

687
01:08:06,687 --> 01:08:08,154
Oh! I'm so sorry.

688
01:08:22,202 --> 01:08:22,827
Where is she going?

689
01:08:27,041 --> 01:08:28,440
Where... are you going?

690
01:08:29,543 --> 01:08:33,070
No no no... This is the
wrong way... it's this way.

691
01:08:33,581 --> 01:08:36,015
No... it's... tch!
We're getting late...

692
01:08:36,216 --> 01:08:42,849
Come on... yes, hurry up

693
01:08:45,559 --> 01:08:46,355
Yes, come on...

694
01:08:49,463 --> 01:08:51,522
Run, run, run!
Yes!

695
01:08:56,737 --> 01:08:58,204
Come on, come on... hurry up.

696
01:08:59,573 --> 01:09:00,597
- Present.

697
01:09:01,408 --> 01:09:03,205
- Present

698
01:09:03,510 --> 01:09:05,205
- Present

