01:13:28,675 --> 01:13:31,303
You're going to try and do thirty.
Thirty words, my foot!

743
01:13:41,154 --> 01:13:44,646
Pass?
- No fail.

744
01:13:50,597 --> 01:13:55,000
No, not in one or two subjects,
you have failed in all of them.

745
01:14:21,028 --> 01:14:24,862
"People celebrate success
but we celebrated failure"

746
01:14:26,266 --> 01:14:29,201
"While eating ice cream
you told me the story of the spider"

747
01:14:30,103 --> 01:14:32,537
"Who after a lot of tries
made her home."

748
01:14:33,273 --> 01:14:36,367
"After all, failure is
the first step towards success..."

749
01:14:37,411 --> 01:14:40,403
"but for me these steps
were never-ending."

750
01:14:47,154 --> 01:14:50,419
Mr. Sahai, how are you?
How is Michelle?

751
01:14:51,291 --> 01:14:54,226
She's all right,
her results have come out.

752
01:14:54,795 --> 01:14:55,659
And what happened?

753
01:14:57,130 --> 01:14:59,064
She has failed again.

754
01:15:01,134 --> 01:15:04,729
But she said that
her papers were easy.

755
01:15:04,938 --> 01:15:10,069
She lied, so she could
enjoy her holidays

756
01:15:12,679 --> 01:15:17,810
But you said that only after falling
can a person rise higher.

757
01:15:19,753 --> 01:15:23,917
Before I fall, I want her
to learn how to fly.

758
01:15:25,025 --> 01:15:29,928
I'm getting old, you know?

759
01:15:30,163 --> 01:15:33,599
Oh no...
- What happened?

760
01:15:34,034 --> 01:15:38,664
Michelle has failed again?
- Yes Paul. I'm worried.

761
01:15:39,006 --> 01:15:39,973
I think Mr Sahai...

762
01:15:43,143 --> 01:15:47,944
Ma... I want to come home.

763
01:15:53,120 --> 01:15:58,285
Ma, I failed.

764
01:16:01,228 --> 01:16:12,196
Teacher shouted at me.

765
01:16:13,040 --> 01:16:14,473
I love you, my baby, I love you.

766
01:16:38,598 --> 01:16:40,998
I was told you were looking
for me Mr. Fernandez

767
01:16:41,835 --> 01:16:46,329
Ah Mr. Sahai, please come in.
I have been waiting for you all day...

768
01:16:47,507 --> 01:16:51,500
I want to share my biggest
achievement with you.

769
01:16:52,179 --> 01:16:53,612
Please have a seat.

770
01:16:58,085 --> 01:17:03,853
Mr. Sahai Michelle has been studying
in the same class for 2 years.

771
01:17:04,758 --> 01:17:07,591
So I thought I would do
something to... help her.

772
01:17:11,264 --> 01:17:14,529
First year Arts, entirely in Braille.

773
01:17:16,269 --> 01:17:21,605
You had once said very few chances
are given for doing good deeds.

774
01:17:22,309 --> 01:17:26,541
I'm happy that you haven't
wasted this chance.

775
01:17:27,481 --> 01:17:30,143
Now no one can stop Michelle
from going ahead. Thank you.

776
01:17:30,383 --> 01:17:34,547
Not at all... It's my duty,
my pleasure, my pride.

777
01:17:38,658 --> 01:17:39,818
I trust that was all right?

778
01:17:48,001 --> 01:17:49,229
Is anything the matter?

779
01:17:52,405 --> 01:17:54,805
Then the books, Mr. Sahai.
Please take them to Michelle.

780
01:18:01,114 --> 01:18:03,082
How do I go out?

781
01:18:05,685 --> 01:18:09,086
How... how do I go out?

782
01:18:10,357 --> 01:18:11,790
I beg your pardon?

783
01:18:12,359 --> 01:18:14,919
The way to go out?

784
01:18:15,929 --> 01:18:18,454
The door, Mr. Sahai...
it's right behind you.

785
01:18:18,865 --> 01:18:20,264
Exactly the way you came in.

786
01:18:24,304 --> 01:18:25,100
Yes...

787
01:18:29,276 --> 01:18:31,938
Mr. Sahai, is everything all right?

788
01:18:50,230 --> 01:18:51,959
Tee... cher...

789
01:19:52,125 --> 01:19:53,854
"New feelings were arising with age..."

790
01:19:54,527 --> 01:19:56,427
"something that I couldn't understand"

791
01:19:57,464 --> 01:20:00,524
"I knew no one besides you teacher"

792
01:20:02,535 --> 01:20:05,936
"That's why I thought of another
relationship with you teacher"

793
01:20:07,040 --> 01:20:08,769
"Was it wrong for me to think this way?"

794
01:20:10,644 --> 01:20:12,043
"A lot was changing..."

795
01:20:12,912 --> 01:20:16,871
"but my failure was constant"

796
01:20:23,990 --> 01:20:26,390
Time up, Michelle... time up.

797
01:20:26,926 --> 01:20:29,121
Michelle, you've already
had extra time.

798
01:20:29,896 --> 01:20:32,888
Michelle... I'll take
the paper out then.

799
01:20:35,769 --> 01:20:37,066
No... no...
- Please...

800
01:20:37,270 --> 01:20:38,237
Leave it...
- Please...

801
01:20:38,438 --> 01:20:41,965
Leave it... no... leave it...

802
01:20:43,076 --> 01:20:45,408
Knowing the answers is not enough...

803
01:20:45,612 --> 01:20:49,605
You have let me down completely.
I am angry... I am very angry...

804
01:20:50,617 --> 01:20:53,916
no... knowing the
answers is not enough...

805
01:20:54,120 --> 01:20:56,145
you need to put them down
on paper too, understand?

806
01:21:03,129 --> 01:21:04,824
Don't just stand there
like a failure!

807
01:21:09,035 --> 01:21:11,503
It's all right.
- No. It's not all right, Mrs. McNally.

808
01:21:12,105 --> 01:21:13,936
It's not only her failure,
it's mine too.

809
01:21:14,441 --> 01:21:16,739
This is the third year in a row
that she's failed.

810
01:21:17,210 --> 01:21:18,939
For three years we have been doing
those same lessons.

811
01:21:19,312 --> 01:21:21,974
She's just too slow at typing.

812
01:21:22,482 --> 01:21:24,347
Hey, Michelle... Michelle...

813
01:21:24,684 --> 01:21:25,946
Where do you think you are going?

814
01:21:26,152 --> 01:21:29,610
Leave this bag...
Leave it, leave it...

815
01:21:29,889 --> 01:21:30,753
Leave this bag!

816
01:21:30,957 --> 01:21:33,517
Enough! I want to go home.

817
01:21:33,727 --> 01:21:35,786
No. No... you're not going anywhere.

818
01:21:35,995 --> 01:21:37,519
I don't want to stay.
I don't want to study.

819
01:21:37,731 --> 01:21:41,292
No... no... You will stay...
you will study. You understand?

820
01:21:41,501 --> 01:21:44,299
You will study. In three years even
the Braille letters have worn out...

821
01:21:44,504 --> 01:21:48,304
but nothing has entered your brain.
- Let her be, Mr. Sahai!

822
01:21:48,541 --> 01:21:51,305
Mrs. McNally, I haven't spent

823
01:21:51,578 --> 01:21:53,478
I'm not going to allow her
to be a failure.

824
01:21:53,747 --> 01:21:55,806
Hey... come here... you...
come here...

825
01:21:56,015 --> 01:21:57,710
Listen, you will...
you will not...

826
01:21:57,817 --> 01:22:02,720
you will not run away from failure.
Understand? Not run away from failure!

827
01:22:04,190 --> 01:22:07,887
Michelle... what is this? Don't you
dare disrespect a book!

828
01:22:08,094 --> 01:22:09,823
Pick it up... Come on.
Pick it up., pick up the book...

829
01:22:10,029 --> 01:22:12,497
pick up the book... Michelle...
Michelle...

830
01:22:12,866 --> 01:22:14,493
Pick up the book...

831
01:22:15,535 --> 01:22:16,160
Stop it

832
01:22:26,713 --> 01:22:29,011
As long as I am alive,
you will study.

833
01:22:29,549 --> 01:22:32,177
I don't want to learn.

834
01:22:32,385 --> 01:22:34,876
Yes! You will learn.
You will graduate.

835
01:22:35,221 --> 01:22:37,883
The black robe. Our dream...

836
01:22:38,391 --> 01:22:43,351
I don't want a robe.
My world is black

837
01:22:43,563 --> 01:22:48,762
No. Your world... your world is
not black. It is full of light!

838
01:22:48,968 --> 01:22:53,701
My world is black, black, black!

839
01:22:53,907 --> 01:22:57,365
Black... black...

840
01:23:25,772 --> 01:23:29,902


841
01:23:31,177 --> 01:23:32,405
in less than 2 minutes.

842
01:23:36,115 --> 01:23:39,084
She's not slow anymore Mrs McNally

843
01:23:41,354 --> 01:23:43,914
Time for celebration.

844
01:23:45,258 --> 01:23:49,126
Time for... an icecream, my dear

845
01:23:51,164 --> 01:23:53,132
Ice-cream?
- Yes...

846
01:23:53,633 --> 01:24:02,666
Mrs. McNally. Life is an ice-cream.
Enjoy it before it melts.

847
01:24:17,624 --> 01:24:18,784
Can I have two?

848
01:24:21,961 --> 01:24:23,360
Ice creams, of course...

849
01:24:29,802 --> 01:24:31,599
Sir... ice-cream...

850
01:24:34,073 --> 01:24:34,801
Ice-cream sir.

851
01:24:42,348 --> 01:24:44,145
What happened?
- Tee...

852
01:24:45,018 --> 01:24:45,814
What's wrong with you?

853
01:24:50,189 --> 01:24:51,156
Your change, sir.

854
01:24:52,992 --> 01:24:54,152
Sir, your change?

855
01:25:25,425 --> 01:25:33,696
Tee... Tee...

856
01:25:39,072 --> 01:25:43,702
tee... tee... tee...

857
01:25:54,587 --> 01:26:01,390
Are you alright?
Call for a doctor!

858
01:26:06,265 --> 01:26:07,061
Mr. Sahai?

859
01:26:09,602 --> 01:26:10,569
Mr. Sahai?

860
01:26:12,138 --> 01:26:14,698
You are here...
I've been looking for you.

861
01:26:16,109 --> 01:26:16,734
Yes?

862
01:26:17,810 --> 01:26:19,141
Don't you recognize me?

863
01:26:19,846 --> 01:26:21,279
It's me... Fernandez

864
01:26:24,283 --> 01:26:25,409
Michelle's Principal.

865
01:26:26,986 --> 01:26:30,717
Oh... yes. Of course.
I'll get Michelle for you.

866
01:26:30,957 --> 01:26:33,653
Michelle!
- Michelle can't hear, Mr. Sahai.

867
01:26:40,099 --> 01:26:43,068
I'll just call her.

868
01:26:46,272 --> 01:26:49,105
Mrs. Gomes!!!
- Michelle is not at home.

869
01:26:55,815 --> 01:26:56,509
She's here.

870
01:27:09,996 --> 01:27:13,625
To forget my name,
to forget the door...

871
01:27:14,333 --> 01:27:18,269
all this is fine... but to forget
Michelle like this...

872
01:27:19,405 --> 01:27:21,339
something is seriously wrong,
Mr. Sahai.

873
01:27:22,008 --> 01:27:24,841
I really think you should
get some help and see a doctor...

874
01:27:28,181 --> 01:27:29,307
Good night. Mr. Sahai.

875
01:28:09,789 --> 01:28:12,849
I'm... sorry.

876
01:28:16,229 --> 01:28:17,890
It's ok.
- It's ok.

877
01:28:19,432 --> 01:28:21,400
Don't ever forget me...

878
01:28:28,741 --> 01:28:29,366
I promise...

879
01:28:30,743 --> 01:28:32,370
I will never forget... you

880
01:28:34,213 --> 01:28:36,943
You worry about me?

881
01:28:40,653 --> 01:28:44,521
No. Don't... worry about me...

882
01:28:46,425 --> 01:28:51,419
just... getting old.

883
01:28:54,634 --> 01:28:57,467
No... Don't worry.

884
01:29:00,606 --> 01:29:03,439
Go to... sleep.

885
01:29:07,680 --> 01:29:10,444
Sing you... a lullaby...

886
01:29:12,218 --> 01:29:13,742
No, I can't sing...

887
01:29:28,601 --> 01:29:35,439
Hush, my baby.
On the treetop.

888
01:29:37,476 --> 01:29:43,904
When the wind blows,
the cradle will rock...

889
01:29:45,885 --> 01:29:48,115
hush my baby...

890
01:29:49,555 --> 01:29:52,490
"A storm had scattered my dreams"

891
01:29:53,159 --> 01:29:55,992
"All those dreams those
were most dear to me"

892
01:29:58,030 --> 01:30:00,965
"That day was the first time
I felt fear..."

893
01:30:02,235 --> 01:30:06,296
"how would I live
if you forget me?"

894
01:30:09,275 --> 01:30:11,470
What happened now?
- She doesn't want to come downstairs

895
01:30:11,644 --> 01:30:14,135
She is feeling awkward to come
in front of your in-laws.

896
01:30:14,347 --> 01:30:15,746
She thinks she'll spoil the evening.

897
01:30:16,115 --> 01:30:17,810
Then why did she bother
coming till here?

898
01:30:18,017 --> 01:30:18,984
Stop it Sara!!!

899
01:30:19,619 --> 01:30:23,680
She's worried about
Mr. Sahai's health, please...

900
01:30:24,257 --> 01:30:26,725
it really hurts me to see
the two of you fight like this...

901
01:30:27,493 --> 01:30:29,017
now you get her ready
and you bring her down.

902
01:30:29,228 --> 01:30:30,388
I have a lot of work to finish...

903
01:30:36,302 --> 01:30:40,170
Michelle, I'm requesting you...

904
01:30:40,773 --> 01:30:43,708
till now whatever you did
was special.

905
01:30:44,477 --> 01:30:47,913
But today is a very
special day for me.

906
01:30:48,614 --> 01:30:52,607
I'm in love and I am getting
engaged before you.

907
01:30:53,286 --> 01:30:54,776
I know this could upset you.

908
01:30:55,221 --> 01:30:57,815
Maybe this evening will
never come in your life

909
01:30:58,391 --> 01:31:00,985
And you may be feeling that
you will never fall in love.

910
01:31:02,862 --> 01:31:05,353
I hope you will.
I really do...

911
01:31:05,898 --> 01:31:07,866
but, until then...

912
01:31:08,234 --> 01:31:13,638
please don't... spoil. My. Evening. Ok?

913
01:31:24,417 --> 01:31:27,875
I am very happy today because all the
people I care about in the world...

914
01:31:28,087 --> 01:31:32,547
are in this room. On this occasion,
I'd love to say a few words.

915
01:31:39,265 --> 01:31:42,462
I'm a very lucky girl that
I got parents like you.

916
01:31:43,269 --> 01:31:44,668
And a sister like Michelle.

917
01:31:45,604 --> 01:31:48,232
I haven't been the best
daughter or the best sister.

918
01:31:48,607 --> 01:31:51,132
But I want to tell you all
I that really love you very much.

919
01:31:52,945 --> 01:31:54,242
And I love this house.

920
01:31:55,448 --> 01:31:57,006
There are so many memories here.

921
01:31:58,451 --> 01:32:01,079
I remember one time Michelle
and I were playing outside.

922
01:32:01,287 --> 01:32:03,585
We were running through
the grass holding hands.

923
01:32:04,290 --> 01:32:08,590
And while running, both of us fell
down and both of us started crying.

924
01:32:09,128 --> 01:32:16,091
Mama and Papa came running outside and
picked up Michelle and left me outside...

925
01:32:17,636 --> 01:32:20,366
and there I was...
with my arms stretched out.

926
01:32:20,639 --> 01:32:21,503
Waiting.

927
01:32:23,642 --> 01:32:24,768
I'm still waiting.

928
01:32:27,646 --> 01:32:31,946
As a child. I...
I used to be so angry with her.

929
01:32:33,486 --> 01:32:36,614
The amount I loved her the
same amount I was jealous of her...

930
01:32:37,156 --> 01:32:39,624
whatever food I didn't like,
I'd feed her.

931
01:32:41,660 --> 01:32:44,959
I used to wake Michelle in the
middle of the night and ask her...

932
01:32:45,664 --> 01:32:49,532
do you want to drink water? Michelle
used to nod her head and say yes...

933
01:32:51,003 --> 01:32:52,971
and I used to turn my head
and go back to sleep.

934
01:32:55,341 --> 01:32:57,138
She would wait for me
all night long.

935
01:33:02,181 --> 01:33:03,648
I can't believe I did that.

936
01:33:08,020 --> 01:33:09,214
Can you Marc?

937
01:33:13,692 --> 01:33:17,560
For all those things that I did,
and all the misplaced...

938
01:33:18,364 --> 01:33:21,231
anger... I'd like to say I'm sorry.

939
01:33:23,702 --> 01:33:24,999
Did I say something wrong?

940
01:33:25,871 --> 01:33:27,839
Then please let me finish.
- I don't want to listen,

941
01:33:28,040 --> 01:33:29,234
It's important to me. Michelle.

942
01:33:43,556 --> 01:33:47,185
Michelle...
- Enough!!!!

943
01:33:55,901 --> 01:33:57,027
Sit down.

944
01:33:59,405 --> 01:34:01,464
SIT... DOWN.

945
01:34:17,256 --> 01:34:19,281
For this joyous and
eventful evening...

946
01:34:21,427 --> 01:34:24,885
Michelle had prepared
a speech for Sara,

947
01:34:25,598 --> 01:34:31,230
I would read and Michelle
would sign...

948
01:34:32,438 --> 01:34:36,738
but I don't think that Michelle
is in any mood for signs.

949
01:34:38,444 --> 01:34:44,576
It's important however, that we
should all hear what she said.

950
01:34:46,952 --> 01:34:53,255
"I was eight years old, wild, violent
always angry at life."

951
01:34:56,462 --> 01:35:00,262
"I felt that I would never experience
the beautiful moments of life."

952
01:35:01,467 --> 01:35:04,595
"Then mother put Sara in my arms
for the first time..."

953
01:35:11,810 --> 01:35:17,112
"and then I knew that I'd see the world
through Sara's eyes."

954
01:35:18,317 --> 01:35:24,222
"Ma says, that I couldn't
stop smiling all day."

955
01:35:30,496 --> 01:35:33,795
"Sara shared all her happiness
with me..."

956
01:35:34,833 --> 01:35:38,030
"she would hold my hand
and take me everywhere."

957
01:35:38,337 --> 01:35:41,033
"When Ma wasn't around
she would feed me..."

958
01:35:41,507 --> 01:35:45,568
"she would wake me at night
and ask me if I wanted water."

959
01:35:51,016 --> 01:35:53,644
"You were the voice
to my silent fingers."

960
01:35:55,854 --> 01:35:58,379
"I am so looking forward
to your wedding day."

961
01:36:00,526 --> 01:36:01,823
"I'll dress up beautifully that day."

962
01:36:10,703 --> 01:36:13,069
"I may never be the bride,
but I will still be the bridesmaid."

963
01:36:18,043 --> 01:36:25,609
"Do teach Marc how to sign,
I have lots to complain about you."

964
01:36:28,220 --> 01:36:30,745
"Thank you for allowing me
to be your bridesmaid, Sara."

965
01:36:32,224 --> 01:36:40,427
"I promise I will not cry... as you
walk with Marc towards a new life."

966
01:36:58,083 --> 01:37:00,449
So on this happy note...

967
01:37:03,756 --> 01:37:04,780
a toast...

968
01:37:07,593 --> 01:37:10,323
for Sara and Marc

969
01:38:09,321 --> 01:38:12,950
Do you, Marc Philip Bragger,
take Sara Maria McNally...

970
01:38:13,158 --> 01:38:16,616
to be you're lawfully wedded wife?
- I do.

971
01:38:17,162 --> 01:38:19,460
Marc... says yes.

972
01:38:19,665 --> 01:38:24,466
Do you, Sara Maria McNally...
- Now the priest is asking Sara...

973
01:38:24,670 --> 01:38:26,535
take Marc Philip Bragger to be
your lawfully wedded husband?

974
01:38:26,739 --> 01:38:28,297
If she agrees...
- I do.

975
01:38:28,507 --> 01:38:30,407
Sara says..."Yes".

976
01:38:31,343 --> 01:38:34,210
I declare you to be man and wife

977
01:38:37,349 --> 01:38:40,648
Now they are exchanging rings.

978
01:38:40,853 --> 01:38:42,150
You may now kiss the bride.

979
01:38:42,354 --> 01:38:48,816
The priest has asked them
to kiss as man and wife.

980
01:38:52,531 --> 01:38:56,331
On the cheek?
- No, no, not on the cheek. On the lips.

981
01:39:45,751 --> 01:39:46,877
Tee...

982
01:39:55,761 --> 01:39:56,625
Te...

983
01:40:06,605 --> 01:40:09,403
What are you doing here?

984
01:40:11,109 --> 01:40:13,407
Wanted... to talk.

985
01:40:29,628 --> 01:40:33,428
Do you love... me?

986
01:40:43,308 --> 01:40:46,106
I'm suffering...

987
01:40:51,483 --> 01:40:56,546
I understand that you are suffering...

988
01:41:00,158 --> 01:41:06,563
I may never know... what it is
to... love... a man.

989
01:41:11,336 --> 01:41:22,144
Maybe you will never
experience physical love

990
01:41:28,186 --> 01:41:29,050
but...

991
01:41:35,360 --> 01:41:40,320
will you kiss me once...

992
01:41:44,870 --> 01:41:45,666
please?

993
01:43:19,965 --> 01:43:20,932
Tee...

994
01:43:26,304 --> 01:43:27,100
Teee...

995
01:43:28,306 --> 01:43:31,503
"In giving me dignity
as a woman..."

996
01:43:31,977 --> 01:43:35,276
"you lost all dignity
as a teacher."

997
01:43:36,314 --> 01:43:38,942
"I realized that
I had asked too much."

998
01:43:39,818 --> 01:43:40,842
"I made a mistake."

999
01:43:41,987 --> 01:43:44,455
"You didn't even give me a chance
to ask for your forgiveness."

1000
01:43:45,824 --> 01:43:47,121
"I'm leaving"

1001
01:43:48,326 --> 01:43:53,195
"Like your walking-stick,
never forget one thing"

1002
01:43:54,332 --> 01:43:59,634
"Darkness is desperately trying
to engulf you"

1003
01:44:00,672 --> 01:44:03,072
"But you must always
walk towards light"

1004
01:44:04,009 --> 01:44:08,412
"Every step of yours, filled with hope,
will keep me alive, Michelle"

1005
01:44:22,027 --> 01:44:24,325
"Once again light transcended
into darkness..."

1006
01:44:25,697 --> 01:44:28,222
"and sound into silence."

1007
01:44:28,867 --> 01:44:34,169
"For twelve years
I walked the path you showed me..."

1008
01:44:35,207 --> 01:44:37,334
"alone in the darkness."

1009
01:44:39,377 --> 01:44:43,438
"When after twelve years I had
found you near the same fountain..."

1010
01:44:44,216 --> 01:44:47,117
"and today after 12 days
this mark sheet."

1011
01:44:47,552 --> 01:44:50,180
"I'm now a graduate in the arts."

1012
01:44:51,223 --> 01:44:53,783
"I want you to be the first one
to hear the good news"

1013
01:44:54,726 --> 01:44:58,025
Mr. Sahai this is your bed,
please lie down.

1014
01:44:58,396 --> 01:45:02,196
Please... that's it. Mr. Sahai...

1015
01:45:02,400 --> 01:45:05,369
This is your bed, Mr. Sahai!

1016
01:45:05,570 --> 01:45:06,366
Nurse!

1017
01:45:07,739 --> 01:45:08,706
Mr. Sahai...

1018
01:45:10,075 --> 01:45:13,203
please lie down... Mr. Sahai

1019
01:45:31,429 --> 01:45:32,225
Tee...

1020
01:45:50,448 --> 01:45:51,244
Teee!

1021
01:45:52,117 --> 01:45:52,845
Tee...

1022
01:45:56,454 --> 01:45:57,318
Tee!

1023
01:46:33,825 --> 01:46:36,453
"Amidst us today there
is a student..."

1024
01:46:36,661 --> 01:46:39,630
who has set an example
of grit and strength...

1025
01:46:40,165 --> 01:46:45,296
and has proved that
nothing is impossible.

1026
01:46:46,338 --> 01:46:48,966
She is the pride of our university.

1027
01:46:49,174 --> 01:46:52,974
And on this rare achievement, I would
want her to say a few words.

1028
01:46:53,178 --> 01:46:56,238
Ladies and Gentleman - Michelle McNally

1029
01:47:03,188 --> 01:47:04,712
That's my daughter.

1030
01:47:21,039 --> 01:47:22,666
After many attempts...

1031
01:47:23,541 --> 01:47:26,840
the spider, in spite of
falling several times...

1032
01:47:27,545 --> 01:47:29,012
has finally made her home.

1033
01:47:30,715 --> 01:47:32,615
The ant has climbed her mountain.

1034
01:47:33,718 --> 01:47:36,346
A tortoise has crossed the dessert...

1035
01:47:37,222 --> 01:47:40,680
and today Michelle McNally,
has finally become a graduate.

1036
01:47:45,897 --> 01:47:48,365
But there is a difference
between you and me.

1037
01:47:48,566 --> 01:47:53,196
What took you 20 years
has taken me 40.

1038
01:47:54,072 --> 01:47:55,699
But I finally did it!

1039
01:48:03,581 --> 01:48:08,712
As a child, I always
lagged behind others.

1040
01:48:11,423 --> 01:48:15,883
My parents were always ashamed of me.

1041
01:48:16,928 --> 01:48:20,989
Every year I would call home
and say, "Ma, I failed."

1042
01:48:23,935 --> 01:48:25,402
But today I can say...

1043
01:48:25,603 --> 01:48:27,662
"Ma, I passed."

1044
01:48:35,280 --> 01:48:39,740
I know that my parents
are very proud of me.

1045
01:48:40,785 --> 01:48:44,482
Telling the world proudly that
I am their daughter

1046
01:48:45,123 --> 01:48:47,148
Thank you Mama, Papa...

1047
01:48:55,967 --> 01:49:04,898
As a child, I was always
searching for something.

1048
01:49:05,643 --> 01:49:08,612
But in the end,
I would only find darkness.

1049
01:49:09,647 --> 01:49:16,109
One day, my mother put me
in those unknown arms.

1050
01:49:17,489 --> 01:49:20,856
He was different from every one.
He was a magician.

1051
01:49:21,493 --> 01:49:28,057
For years he dragged me from
darkness into the light.

1052
01:49:31,336 --> 01:49:34,066
When it comes to God,
we are all blind.

1053
01:49:34,672 --> 01:49:37,869
None of you have ever
seen Him or heard Him.

1054
01:49:39,177 --> 01:49:44,638
But I have touched God.
I have felt his presence.

1055
01:49:46,017 --> 01:49:49,680
I call him "Tee.

1056
01:49:57,862 --> 01:49:59,762
For me everything was BLACK

1057
01:50:02,200 --> 01:50:07,502
But my teacher taught me
the new meaning of Black

1058
01:50:11,876 --> 01:50:15,437
Black is not only darkness
and suffocation.

1059
01:50:18,716 --> 01:50:20,513
It is the colour of achievement.

1060
01:50:21,886 --> 01:50:23,251
The colour of knowledge.

1061
01:50:25,557 --> 01:50:28,025
The colour of the graduation robe.

1062
01:50:28,726 --> 01:50:30,591
The colour that we all share today.

1063
01:50:32,730 --> 01:50:34,595
But there is a difference
between you and me.

1064
01:50:34,899 --> 01:50:38,130
Today you all wear this
to celebrate graduation.

1065
01:50:38,570 --> 01:50:39,537
But not me.

1066
01:50:41,906 --> 01:50:46,002
Because I want my teacher
to be the first one to see me...

1067
01:50:46,611 --> 01:50:49,045
wear this black robe.

1068
01:50:56,421 --> 01:51:00,380
Every graduation day,
he brought me here.

1069
01:51:01,092 --> 01:51:03,959
Every year, we would stand
near that door...

1070
01:51:04,429 --> 01:51:07,489
and every year he would
write in my hand...

1071
01:51:08,099 --> 01:51:12,229
"One day I want to see you
on that stage Michelle"

1072
01:51:15,273 --> 01:51:16,570
It has taken me 40 years...

1073
01:51:16,774 --> 01:51:18,833
to fulfill his dream.

1074
01:51:19,777 --> 01:51:24,077
And today, for the first time,
I feel my lack of sight.

1075
01:51:24,782 --> 01:51:32,746
Because I want to see my teacher
standing at the door...

1076
01:51:32,957 --> 01:51:34,925
watching me fulfill our dream
with pride

1077
01:51:59,083 --> 01:52:00,050
"Teacher..."

1078
01:53:50,928 --> 01:53:58,733
"Our dream"...Tee... Woah...

1079
01:54:53,991 --> 01:54:54,787
Woah... woah

1080
01:55:05,336 --> 01:55:05,961
Woah

1081
01:55:08,005 --> 01:55:09,131
Woah...

1082
01:55:19,016 --> 01:55:19,983
Tee... Woah

1083
01:55:24,689 --> 01:55:25,553
woah

1084
01:55:42,039 --> 01:55:47,500
"Dear Ms. Nair, you'll be happy to
know that we have come into the light:

1085
01:55:48,880 --> 01:55:54,011
"Today my teacher has remembered
his first word - Water."

1086
01:55:55,386 --> 01:55:57,354
"He is the greatest teacher
in the world..."

1087
01:55:57,722 --> 01:56:02,182
"who has proved again that there is
nothing impossible in this world."

1088
01:56:03,060 --> 01:56:07,690
"Who has taught me that there is so much
happiness in living for someone else"

1089
01:56:08,399 --> 01:56:11,596
"Today is my teacher's
first day at school Miss Nair."

1090
01:56:12,069 --> 01:56:16,699
And his alphabets, just like mine,
will not start with A, B, C, D, and E.

1091
01:56:17,241 --> 01:56:22,543
But with B, L, A, C, K

1092
01:56:23,581 --> 01:56:24,605
"BLACK"